@# $MirBSD: src/share/man/man0/COPYRIGHT,v 1.31 2004/10/10 16:56:21 tg Exp $
# $OpenBSD: COPYRIGHT,v 1.2 2001/01/29 02:11:07 niklas Exp $
# @@(#)COPYRIGHT	5.1 (Berkeley) 7/1/91

This file contains the licencing information for code released by the
MirOS Project, a loosely bound group of developers, mainly in Europe,
who develops and delivers an Open Source(TM) operating system and as-
sorted utilities and offsprings, some of which are MirOS BSD (and the
other kernel flavours), the MirPorts Framework, MirbsdKsh, MirMake.
Please note that, despite our efforts to achieve this, the MirOS sys-
tem as a whole is, due to the variety of licences used when combining
the compilation, not "OSI certified Open Source software", but we be-
lieve that all work the "MirOS Project" consists of, whether documen-
tation, code or artwork, meets the Open Source Definition; we too try
to ensure that all work delivered by us, even that is not part of the
MirOS Project, such as documentation to the GNU Binutils and Compiler
Collection, or the patches in MirPorts, are freely redistributable as
common in the open source community.


The MirOS Project licences their compilations under the following
terms and conditions:

